cPanel-PublicAPI

cPanel::PublicAPI is a simple interface for accessing cPanel & WHM's APIs.
This module is developed with a "fall back" dependency design, which means that
if one of several modules is not available, it will fallback on the next.

The module that this will fall back on are (in this order):

JSON::Syck
JSON::XS
JSON
JSON::PP

The required modules for operations are:

IO::Socket
IO::Socket::SSL
URI::Escape

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc cPanel::PublicAPI

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=cPanel-PublicAPI

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/cPanel-PublicAPI

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/cPanel-PublicAPI

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/cPanel-PublicAPI/


